entries.femaleVariant: How's working with Dakota?
How ya like workin' with Dakota?
Fine, I guess. Nothin' to compare to. Never take jobs from fixers.
Never as in never-ever? Dakota's your first?
No... That was Tony Izoria. Two decades back.
Still had your baby teeth back then.
Twenty years? You woulda still had baby teeth back then.
You owe me, if I recall.
Think you still owe me one.
That I do. What do you need?
And nimbler fingers. Age wasn't an issue for Tony.
He... do somethin' to you?
Mh-hm. He left me trapped in ventilation shaft in a Kang Tao warehouse. Seventy eight hours.
Guess he had to delay the job, figured I'd hold up all right. No water, no food, no contact.
And then?
I thought they were all dead, that the Chinese were hunting me. Heard 'em talking, but didn't understand a word.
Eventually, I quit, scaled a shaft up to the roof. Five floors up, didn't see any choice but to jump.
You owe me, if I recall.
You lived.
The moral being all fixers are dicks?
What happened to Toni?
But you survived.
You owe me, if I recall.
So, uh, whatever happened to Toni?
There a moral here? All fixers are dickheads?
Tragic elevator accident. Of all the things, right?
I mean, that kinda stuff just doesn't happen nowadays.
Most important parts of me, at least.
Know how much I weigh? 260.
I'm in more danger of rusting up than bleeding out.
'Bout ninety percent. Pieced together most of the chrome myself. Little hobby of mine.
This's all RealSkinn?
Mh-hm. And invest in good translation tech.
Anyway, when I fell, it was Kang Tao corpos who found me, slapped me back together.
Not much choice but to work there a few years after that, but they were all right.
